Use the standard library
This is how to has_close_elements of numbers and threshold:
   Remember that n is numbers's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that j is sum of i and 1
      Remember that rest is diff of n and j
      Do this rest times:
         Remember that a is item i in numbers
         Remember that b is item j in numbers
         Remember that d is abs of (diff of a and b)
         When d is less than threshold, then:
            The answer is 1
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is 0
Now you know
>>> has_close_elements of [1, 2, 3] and 0.500000
0
>>> has_close_elements of [1, 2.800000, 3, 4, 5, 2] and 0.300000
1
>>> has_close_elements of [1.000000, 2.000000, 3.900000, 4.000000, 5.000000, 2.200000] and 0.300000
1